Genre(s).......: Comedy / Crime / Drama

Brilliant, but socially inept, forensic anthropologist Dr. Temperence 
Brennan works at the Jeffersonian Institute in Washington DC. After 
consulting for him on a FBI case, she is approached by cocky yet charming 
ex-Army Ranger turned Special Agent, Seeley Booth to help the Bureau 
solve crimes by identifying human remains that are too far gone for 
standard FBI forensic investigations. Brennan's empirical, literal view 
of the world causes friction with Booths emotive, instinctive attitude 
creating a volatile relationship. However as their case load increases 
the symbiotic partnership produces results and with the support of 
Brennan's Squint Squad, murderers, past and present should be on the 
look out.
